  "texts": [
    "The advantages of this approach are that (a) minimal expertise and computational resources are required, (b) there is virtually no computation spent on altering the model parameters, and (c) GPT-4 is a versatile model to start with.",
    "Some of the limitations include potential security and privacy issues due to the need to upload information to the LLM server, limited customization capabilities, and high inference cost and latency. 3.",
    "Prompt Learning: these are approaches that extend traditional prompt engineering by incorporating trainable parameters to optimize prompt representations, improving model adaptability.",
    "Methods such as prefix-tuning [42], P-tuning [41], and prompt tuning [40] adjust learned prompt embeddings (trainable prompt representations in a neural network, stored as numerical vectors instead of human-readable text) to better steer the model's behavior while keeping the core model parameters frozen.",
    "For example, prompt learning has been used to customize LLMs for clinical diagnosis [56]."
  ]
